Parliament, Tuesday 24 April 2018 – The National Assembly today agreed that the Portfolio Committee on Police could introduce the Independent Police Investigative Directorate Amendment Bill. The House also passed three Bills. The Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) Amendment Bill aims to amend the existing Ipid Act to align it with Constitutional Court provisions inserted in the court’s judgment of 2016. These dealt with the powers of the Minister of Police to take disciplinary steps or to remove the Ipid Executive Director, among other things. The three Bills passed by the National Assembly’s plenary sitting today - and which now have to go to the National Council of Provinces for consideration - are the: Owing to court proceedings still pending, the National Assembly referred the report about Mr Manyaba Rubben Mohlaloga, the Council Chairperson of the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa, back to the Portfolio Committee on Communications for further consideration and report. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Enquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 A joint committee of Parliament monitors improvements in the quality of life and status of women in South Africa.Read more